VO DAT CONG KHANH is an Intern AI Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience, building a strong foundational skill set through academic and personal projects. Their core expertise lies in advanced Artificial Intelligence and Deep Learning techniques, specifically focusing on Large Language Models (LLMs) and Transformer architectures. They possess hands-on experience with Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), including Supervised Fine-tuning (SFT), Direct Preference Optimization (DPO), and Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO), alongside efficient fine-tuning methods like LoRA and Unsloth. Notably, they successfully implemented a full RLHF pipeline to fine-tune the Qwen2.5-1.5B model for a Vietnamese healthcare chatbot, demonstrating proficiency in optimizing LLMs using both expert-curated data and automated evaluation via LLM-as-judge, where DPO significantly improved response quality.
Technically, they are proficient in Python and JavaScript, leveraging frameworks such as PyTorch, Hugging Face Transformers, and TRL for model development. They have practical experience with databases including Microsoft SQL Server, MongoDB, and PostgreSQL, and are familiar with development tools like TensorBoard for experiment tracking and Github for version control. Further skills encompass Machine Learning, Data Structures and Algorithms, Knowledge Discovery and Data Mining, and Reward Modeling, all contributing to their comprehensive understanding of AI system development.